longBusinessSummary: Jaxon Mining Inc. operates as a mineral exploration and development company in Canada. The company explores for silver, gold, zinc, copper, and lead deposits. It holds interests in the Red Springs Project, which consists of 17 mineral claims that covers an area of 261.57 km2 located in northwest British Columbia; Netalzul Mountain Project that comprises of 20 claims, which covers an area of 104.22 km2 located in the north of Smithers, British Columbia; Max Project, which consists of 6 mineral claims covering an area of 90 km2; and Blunt Mountain that consists of 12 mineral claims covering an area of 72 km2 located in the north of Smithers in British Columbia. The company was formerly known as Jaxon Minerals Inc. and changed its name to Jaxon Mining Inc. in August 2017. Jaxon Mining Inc. was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
